INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (24,'1516604234-280','White Canary','https://www.superherodb.com/white-canary/10-10542/',65,10,35,15,50,90,'-','No alter egos found.','Silk Sister, Sara Lance','-','Birds of Prey #1','DC Comics','bad','Female','Human','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','Brown','Black','-','-','League of Assassins,Living Assault Weapons,Extreme Justice,Justice Legion Alpha','-','White Canary''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/white-canary/10-10542/history/','Also contained within the briefcase is a message declaring that every hour a name from the briefcase will be killed until the Birds of Prey stop the carnage. After speculating on the possible identity of the killer, a signal light is seen just over the skyline much in the same way the Bat-Signal is used causing the Birds of Prey to track its source. Upon arriving they find the Penguin cowering and pleading to a shadowy figure to spare his life. Blinded by the light the mysterious figure''s face remains hidden, yet Black Canary deduces from the posturing that the figure has a sense of royalty, and is most likely Asian. Immediately two names flash through her mind, Cassandra Cain, or Lady Shiva. Without warning the shadow attacks, easily taking down Black Canary and disarming the Huntress.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10542.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (25,'1516608053-5217','Gamora','https://www.superherodb.com/gamora/10-65/',75,85,45,85,55,100,'Gamora Zen Whoberi Ben Titan','No alter egos found.','The Deadliest Woman In The Universe, The Most Dangerous Woman in the Galaxy','Planet Zen Whoberi, Silican System, Milky Way','Strange Tales #180 (June, 1975)','Marvel Comics','good','Female','Zen-Whoberian','6''0 // 183 cm','170 lb // 77 kg','Yellow','Black','Assassin, mercenary, adventurer','C.I.T.T.; formerly Godthab Omega, Monster Island, Sanctuary II and the pocket-dimension within the Soul Gem; Earth-7528','Guardians of the Galaxy,Marvel Knights','Thanos (foster father), Thane (foster brother), Unnamed former Symbiote','Gamora''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/gamora/10-65/history/','Yet another universal threat emerged when Adam Warlock''s good side sought to eradicate the universe of all sin by simply eradicating the universe itself. However, Gamora (and many of Earth''s heroes, including fellow Infinity Watch member Moondragon) was manipulated into joining the Goddess'' crusade. A war broke out between those manipulated and those non-manipulated with both side suffering heavy casualties. Those manipulated were broke out of trance when Warlock and Thanos defeated the Goddess and banished her to soul world.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/65.jpg');
