INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (70,'1516607729-4803','Hawkeye','https://www.superherodb.com/hawkeye/10-73/',60,15,25,10,30,80,'Clinton Francis Barton','Goliath, Ronin','Ronin, Goliath, Golden Archer, the Marksman, Father Time, Longbow','Waverly, Iowa','Tales of Suspense #57 (September, 1964)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Human','6''3 // 191 cm','230 lb // 104 kg','Blue','Blond','Adventurer','-','Hawkeye & Mockingbird,Avengers West Coast,The Ultimates,The Mighty Avengers,S.H.I.E.L.D.,Thunderbolts,Avengers,Black Cat''s Gang,A.I.M.,Marvel Knights,Avenging Host,Defenders','Harold Barton (father, deceased), Edith Barton (mother, deceased), Bernard Barton (brother, deceased), Barbara Morse (wife, deceased)','Hawkeye''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/hawkeye/10-73/history/','As War Machine, Rhodes investigated and was surprised to see Hawkeye among the rebels. A government-backed group led by USAgent also arrived adding further confusion between the \"Brothers in Arms\". The three were able to stop the conflict and were confronted by the mysterious Advisor.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/73.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (73,'1516608138-5480','Flash II','https://www.superherodb.com/flash-ii/10-892/',90,50,100,60,100,60,'Bartholomew Henry Allen','Black Racer','The Scarlet Speedster, the Fastest Man Alive, the Monarch of Motion, the Sultan of Speed','Fallville, Iowa','Showcase #4 (October, 1956)','DC Comics','good','Male','Black Racer','6''0 // 183 cm','195 lb // 88 kg','Blue','Blond','Forensic Scientist','Central City, Missouri','Flash Family,Justice League Antarctica,Flash Family,Superfriends,Flash,Flash,Justice League of America,Blue Lantern Corps,Justice League,Justice Legion Alpha','Henry and Nora (parents), Malcolm Thawne (twin), Iris West Allen (wife), Wally West (Flash III, nephew), Don and Dawn Allen (son and daughter), Bart Allen (Flash IV, grandson), Jenni Ognats (granddaughter)','Flash II''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/flash-ii/10-892/history/','As Flash and Hot Pursuit fight, Hot Pursuit''s club detects the actual anomaly. Hot Pursuit goes after the anomaly, and Flash and Kid Flash follow him. The anomaly is in fact Professor Zoom, who is attacking Patty. The Flash takes Patty to safety, and Patty reveals to him that Zoom transformed himself into the boy the police found in Jay Nicolosi''s murder scene. The Flash then returns to attacks Zoom. Hot Pursuit uses his stick to drain the Speed Force out of Zoom, and tells the Flash and Kid Flash to evacuate the building because when the Speed Force process ends, everything within one hundred feet will age to dust. The Flash and Kid Flash evacuate the building, but Zoom overcomes Hot Pursuit''s club and kills him. The Flash and Kid Flash pursue Zoom to a park, but Zoom disgusises himself as an old man, and the two heroes lose him. The Flash and Kid Flash then check up on Hot Pursuit''s empty suit, and the Flash reveals to Kid Flash that Thawne is the one who killed his mother.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/892.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (74,'1516609221-6874','Brundlefly','https://www.superherodb.com/brundlefly/10-10642/',70,35,25,40,35,15,'Sethaniel Brundle','No alter egos found.','The Fly','-','The Fly (1986)','','neutral','Male','Mutant','6''4 // 193 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','Scientist','-','','-','Brundlefly''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/brundlefly/10-10642/history/','In the fifth stage which appears only in a deleted scene, Brundle can no longer wear clothes and his body is becoming an infected-looking mess of deteriorated flesh and growths, while a fly limb emerges from the growth on his side. In the sixth stage, Brundle''s head has become misshapen and almost all of his hair is gone. His body has also deteriorated even further, as he walks with a hunch and his some of his fingers appear to be partially fused.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10642.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (75,'1516608172-5553','Firestorm','https://www.superherodb.com/firestorm/10-10395/',40,80,60,80,100,40,'Ronald Raymond','No alter egos found.','Ronnie, Roy, Ronald Rockwell, Flamehead','-','Firestorm #1 (March, 1978)','DC Comics','good','Male','Human','6''2 // 188 cm','202 lb // 91 kg','Blue','Auburn','Adventurer; former employee of Bun ''n Run','Formerly Manhattan, New York City; Ivy University, Ivy Town; Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania','Black Lantern Corps,Justice Legion Alpha,Firestorm Matrix,Superfriends','Edward Raymond (father); Elaine Rockwell (mother, deceased); Felicity Smoak-Raymond (stepmother); Richard Dare (grandfather)','Firestorm''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/firestorm/10-10395/history/','Palmer manages to separate Jason and Ronnie, but not before the Firestorm matrix causes a huge explosion, transmutating everything in the Professor''s laboratory into table salt. While recovering in the hospital, Stein explains to Ronnie that it seems to be very dangerous to fuse into Firestorm again. Also, it is revealed that Ronnie, after quickly leaving the hospital and being threatened by Jason''s father to stay away from Jason, lied to everyone, as he seems to perfectly remember murdering Gehenna as a Black Lantern.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10395.jpg');
