INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (93,'1516607438-4374','Iron Man','https://www.superherodb.com/iron-man/10-85/',100,85,60,85,100,65,'Anthony Edward Stark','No alter egos found.','Iron Knight, Hogan Potts, Spare Parts Man, Cobalt Man II, Crimson Dynamo, Ironman','Long Island, New York','Tales of Suspence #39 (March, 1963)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Human','6''6 // 198 cm','425 lb // 191 kg','Blue','Black','Inventor, Industrialist; former United States Secretary of Defense','Seattle, Washington','S.H.I.E.L.D.,Contingency,Illuminati,The Ultimates,Avenging Host,Hulkbusters,Marvel Knights,Avengers,Guardians of the Galaxy,The Mighty Avengers,Avengers West Coast','Howard Anthony Stark (father, deceased), Maria Stark (mother, deceased), Morgan Stark (cousin), Isaac Stark (ancestor)','Iron Man''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/iron-man/10-85/history/','Stark returned to work at a hectic pace, often sleeping in his lab. A former classmate asked for help--a super soldier project named Extremis had been given to a small terrorist group. Iron Man battled the augmented terrorist Mallen, but suffered massive injuries. Taking Extremis, Iron Man healed and found himself able to directly interface with technology, especially the armor. Going after Mallen again, Stark was forced to kill him.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/85.jpg');
