INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (143,'1516607969-5112','Gladiator','https://www.superherodb.com/gladiator/10-1521/',50,100,100,100,80,70,'Kallark','No alter egos found.','Majestor, Praetor, Captain Universe','-','X-Men Vol 1 #107 October, 1977','Marvel Comics','neutral','Male','Strontian','6''6 // 198 cm','595 lb // 268 kg','Blue','Blue','Majestor of the Shi''ar Empire; Former Praetor of the Imperial Guard; possibly former Herald of Galactus','Chandilar, Shi''ar Galaxy; mobile throughout the Shi''ar Empire and surrounding galaxies.','Gods,Annihilators,Imperial Guard','Kubark (Kid Gladiator) (son), Xenith (The Strontian) (cousin)','Gladiator''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/gladiator/10-1521/history/','In time Phoenix turned to Dark Phoenix, a major threat. In the Imperial Center, ruling seat of the ShiÃ¯Â¿Â½ar Empire, Empress Lilandra and her ministers of the Grand Council observe a viewing screen. They see the Dark Phoenix approach Earth. Gladiator stood in guard at the Center.  Lilandra started speaking, comparing the threat posed by the Dark Phoenix to Galactus. Yet she argued, the new threat was greater than the old one. Both beings felt infernal hunger and the need to consume. But Galactus consumed only individual worlds, while the Dark Phoenix could consume everything in existence. Lilandra decided that the Dark Phoenix had to be destroyed for the universe to survive.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/1521.jpg');
