INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (205,'1516606724-3454','Man-Thing','https://www.superherodb.com/man-thing/10-382/',50,35,10,100,100,40,'Dr. Theodore Sallis','No alter egos found.','the Vagornus Koth; the Swamp Walker; Mr. Salad; Walking Mulch Heap','-','Savage Tales #1 (May, 1971)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','null','7''0 // 213 cm','500 lb // 225 kg','Red','No Hair','-','Man-Thing''s Swamp, Citrusville, Florida','Midnight Sons,A.R.M.O.R.,Thunderbolts','Ellen Brandt (ex-wife) Job Burke (son)','Man-Thing''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/man-thing/10-382/history/','Upon completing his new serum, Ted committed its formula to memory and burnt his records. When Ellen led Ted into an AIM ambush, he fled and injected the only existing sample of the serum into himself just before his car crashed into the swamp. He should have died, but the magical energies of the swamp combined with the serum to transform him into the hideous creature later known as the Man-Thing. His intelligence rapidly fading, he slew the AIM agents and horribly burned half of Ellen''s face. Unknown to Sallis, Ellen had been pregnant.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/382.jpg');
