INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (330,'1516605106-1514','Solomon Grundy','https://www.superherodb.com/solomon-grundy/10-782/',10,95,15,100,95,30,'Cyrus Gold','No alter egos found.','Marshland Monster','Gotham City','All-American Comics #61 (October, 1944)','DC Comics','bad','Male','Zombie','9''2 // 279 cm','971 lb // 437 kg','Black','White','-','-','Extreme Justice,Black Lantern Corps,All-Star Squadron','Unnamed wife (deceased); Karin Rykel (possible descendant, deceased); Chrissie Cavendish (possible descendant)','Solomon Grundy''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/solomon-grundy/10-782/history/','Another possibility is given by a mysterious group called the Seven Unknown Men of Slaughter Swamp. They recount the death of a miserly pedophile, Cyrus Gold, at the hands of an enraged mob. However, they also mention that Gold could just as easily have been the innocent victim of a misunderstanding, as Slaughter Swamp is a point in space where time means nothing. The same Unknown Man who tells the tale, punishes another of his group, the Eighth Man: Zor, by dressing him in Cyrus Gold''s clothing and leaving him for the mob to find, implying that Zor (an extremely vain character, notable for attempting several times to overthrow the Universe and for having defeated the Spectre) would later become the first Solomon Grundy.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/782.jpg');
