INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (375,'1516609627-7350','Birdman','https://www.superherodb.com/birdman/10-1506/',0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ray Randal','No alter egos found.','Bird-Man, Harvey Birdman, Ray Randal, Harvey Birdman Attorney at Law, Harry, Henry, Birdbath, Bootyliciuos','-','Birdman and the Galaxy Trio (1967)','Hanna-Barbera','good','Male','God / Eternal','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','-','-','','-','Birdman''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/birdman/10-1506/history/','Birdman faced several super villains though most were either one-shot characters or appeared in two episodes. The one constant was the employer of most of them, F.E.A.R. . A secret organizations whose members wore hoods and addressed each other by codenumbers. The leader was Number One.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/1506.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (385,'1516610304-8048','Alan Scott','https://www.superherodb.com/alan-scott/10-698/',65,80,25,90,100,35,'Alan Ladd Wellington Scott','No alter egos found.','Green Lantern, White King, Sentinal','Gotham City','All-American Comics 16 (1940)','DC Comics','good','Male','null','5''11 // 180 cm','201 lb // 90 kg','Blue','Blond','-','Gotham City and New York City; Formerly Capitol City','Green Lantern Corps,All-Star Squadron,Justice Society of America','Harlequin (Molly Mayne-Scott) (wife), Thorn (Rose Canton) (first wife, deceased), Todd Rice (Obsidian, son), Jennie-Lynn Hayden (Jade, daughter, deceased)','Alan Scott''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/alan-scott/10-698/history/','Jennie-Lynn and Todd, who developed superhuman powers as a result of their father''s connection to the mystic Starheart, did not meet until adolescence, and set out to uncover the identities of their real parents. They adopted the costumed identities of Jade and Obsidian and confronted Alan about their parentage. And truly, Alan had no clue. Also during this time, he renewed his acquaintance with Molly and discovered her past as the Harlequin; the pair finally gave in to their longtime attraction. But Rose Canton also resurfaced. Just before her death, she revealed the circumstances of Jennie and Todd''s births. Alan and Molly were married, but soon separated by the JSA''s banishment to Limbo. They were reunited two years later when the Justice Society returned to Earth.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/698.jpg');
