INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (432,'1516607396-4295','Jack-Jack','https://www.superherodb.com/jack-jack/10-871/',10,35,70,80,100,10,'Jac-jack Parr','No alter egos found.','-','-','The Incredibles (Movie, 2004)','Dark Horse Comics','good','Male','Human','2''4 // 71 cm','30 lb // 14 kg','Blue','Brown','-','-','Incredible Family,Violet Parr','Robert Parr(Mr Incredible, father), Helen Parr (Elastigirl, mother), Violet Parr(Violet, sister), Dashiell Parr (Dash, brother)','Jack-Jack''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/jack-jack/10-871/history/','Three months later, Jack-Jack is seen with his family at Dash''s track race. After the race, The Underminer emerges from underneath the earth and declares war, and the family, including Jack-Jack, put on their masks.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/871.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (434,'1516608383-5769','Elastigirl','https://www.superherodb.com/elastigirl/10-870/',65,35,35,95,55,70,'Helen Parr','No alter egos found.','Mrs Incredible','-','The Incredibles (Movies, 2004)','Dark Horse Comics','good','Female','Human','5''6 // 168 cm','125 lb // 56 kg','Brown','Brown','-','-','Violet Parr,Incredible Family','Robert Parr(Mr Incredible, husband), Violet Parr(Violet, daughter), Dashiell Parr (Dash, son), Jack-jack (son)','Elastigirl''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/elastigirl/10-870/history/','Bob, however, does not adjust well to civilian life. Frustrated in his job at Insuricare under a tyrannical boss named Mr. Huph, Bob escapes the monotony of his seemingly average life by sneaking out with his best friend Frozone (Lucius Best) to secretly continue hero work. They get away with this for awhile using the cover story that they''re bowling, but Helen eventually finds out, and this leads to conflict and tension between Helen and Bob.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/870.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (436,'1516607619-4671','Hercules','https://www.superherodb.com/hercules/10-78/',65,100,50,85,90,100,'Heracles','No alter egos found.','Spider-Herc, The Lion of Olympus, The Defender of Olympus, The Scion of Olympus, Prince of Power, Alcaeus, Herakles, Herc, Harry Cleese, Victor Tegler, Agent 74','Thebes, Greece','-','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Demi-God','6''5 // 196 cm','325 lb // 146 kg','Blue','Brown','Adventurer, Olympian God of Strength and Labor, later Olympian God of Heroes','Brooklyn; formerly Infinite Avengers Mansion, Mount Olympus, Avengers Mansion, Hydrobase','Champions,Olympians,Champions of Los Angeles,God Squad,Gods','-','Hercules''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/hercules/10-78/history/','Upon meeting up with Athena the trio set out to San Fransico to assemble a team of gods from Earth (Snowbird, Tecumotzin, Amatsu-Mikaboshi, and Atum the God Eater) to battle and defeat the Skrull Gods Kly''bn and Sl''gur''t. In route to Skrull space through the dream realm they battled Nightmare, and recived his map of the dream realm. Hercules and Narya made love after she confessed to him that she didn''t want to be alone anymore. Soon after a Skrull who had been with them since the end of World War Hulk revealed itself and was quickly dispatched. However, Hercules and Snowbird together managed to slay the head god of the Skrulls, destroying the very inspiration for the ongoing Secret Invasion war. Meanwhile Mikaboshi managed to overcome SlÃ¯Â¿Â½gurÃ¯Â¿Â½t, and apparently assumed the position of leader of the Skrull pantheon, all according to Athena''s plan.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/78.jpg');
