INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (465,'1516609448-7018','Blade','https://www.superherodb.com/blade/10-33/',65,30,40,50,40,90,'Eric Brooks','No alter egos found.','Switchblade, Frank Blade, Daywalker','Soho, London,England','Tomb of Dracula Vol. 1 #10 (1973)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Vampire','6''2 // 188 cm','215 lb // 97 kg','Brown','Black','Vampire hunter, former private investigator.','Mobile','Vampires,Marvel Knights,Howling Commandos,Midnight Sons','Tara Brooks (mother)','Blade''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/blade/10-33/history/','The mother of all demons, Lilith, hired Blade''s agency to kill Ghost Rider -- the leather-clad, motorcycle-riding Spirit of Vengeance -- and bad-boy John Blaze, the fiery skeleton''s former host. After a protracted battle, Blade and company realized they had been duped. The team joined with Ghost Rider and Blaze against Lilith, battling her monstrous minion Meatmarket. Blade, Drake and King continued their partnership with Ghost Rider and Blaze. Along with Dr. Strange, Morbius the Living Vampire and the Darkhold Redeemers, they formed the Midnight Sons, a group dedicated to preserving the boundaries between our world and the dark realms. The Midnight Sons clashed with Lilith and her demonspawn, the Lilin, in a supernatural contest with Earth as the prize. The Midnight Sons proved victorious, destroying Lilith and her brood.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/33.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (468,'1516609297-6926','Boom-Boom','https://www.superherodb.com/boom-boom/10-400/',40,10,15,45,60,65,'Tabitha Smith','Meltdown','Time Bomb, Boomer, Meltdown, Tabby, Firecracker, Mutate #35, Nancy Forrester','-','Secret Wars II #5','Marvel Comics','good','Female','Mutant','5''5 // 165 cm','122 lb // 55 kg','Blue','Blond','Adventurer, former student, thief','-','Genoshan Mutates,X-Force,Utopians,Fallen Angels,X-Factor,Nextwave,New Mutants,Underground,X-Terminators','-','Boom-Boom''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/boom-boom/10-400/history/','Tabitha relocated with the rest of the X-men to San Francisco. On a shopping spree, she encountered Nuwa wreaking havoc on the local shopping scene. After researching Nuwa''s weakness, Tabitha defeated her new enemy.\n\nLater abducted by anti-mutant extremists, the Sapien League, alongside Surge and Hellion. Tabitha was held hostage by their leader, the Leper Queen when the mutant strike force X-Force invaded her headquarters looking for the lost mutants. When X-Force were forcibly transported into the future by Cyclops, the Leper Queen, angry at not being killed by the team, shot Tabitha in the head. Arriving just prior to the shot, X-23 managed to prevent Tabitha''s death by shooting the Leper Queen.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/400.jpg');
