INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (509,'1516604172-87','Wonder Girl','https://www.superherodb.com/wonder-girl/10-1497/',75,90,25,80,40,60,'Cassandra Elizabeth Sandsmark','No alter egos found.','Cassandra Sandsmark, Cassie, Helen Troy, Wonder Woman, Cassie Sandsmark','-','Wonder Woman (vol. 2) #105 (January 1996)','DC Comics','good','Female','Demi-God','5''5 // 165 cm','114 lb // 51 kg','Blue','Blond','-','-','Young Justice,Teen Titans,Teen Titans West','-','','','','Wonder Girl''s powers','https://www.superherodb.com/wonder-girl/10-1497/powers/','[{\"powers\":\"Cassandra originally received her powers from a number of mystical artifacts employed by Artemis during her time as Wonder Woman. These included the Gauntlet of Atlas and the Sandals of Hermes, which provided her with the powers of strength and speed/flight, respectively. She was eventually granted similar abilities by Zeus as \"\"her fondest wish.\"\" Discouraged by previously shown arrogance in his children (Ares and Heracles), Zeus also blessed Cassandra''s mother with the ability to take away her powers for a short time via a simple touch.\"},{\"powers\":\"Shortly after joining the Teen Titans, Ares approached her and gave Cassandra her own magic lasso. Unlike Wonder Woman''s Lasso of Truth, Cassandra''s is a weapon which channels Zeus'' lightning when she becomes angry. When the Greek gods left the mortal plane as a result of the events of Infinite Crisis, taking Cassandra''s powers along with them, Ares offered her some of his power, saying that she would be \"\"more powerful than [she''s] ever been\"\". What this entails is not made entirely clear, though she appeared to have retained all of her former abilities. In a storyline taking place \"\"One Year Later\"',' Cassie was shown catching a falling jet',' which she was surprised at being able to accomplish. However',' while trying to stop the military from detaining her mother',' Ares causes her powers to fluctuate when he believes she is wasting them on frivolous matters.\"\"}','{\"\"powers\"\":\"\"Ares in the end was not');
