INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (647,'1516607405-4308','Jack of Hearts','https://www.superherodb.com/jack-of-hearts/10-86/',65,55,100,30,80,30,'Jonathan Hart','No alter egos found.','-','New Haven, Connecticut','Deadly Hands of Kung Fu #22 (March, 1976)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Human','5''1 // 155 cm','175 lb // 79 kg','Blue / White','Brown','Adventurer','Avengers Mansion','Avengers','Philip (father, deceased), Marie (mother)','Jack of Hearts''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/jack-of-hearts/10-86/history/','Jack remained with the Avengers for several missions, including those against the time-traveling Kang when he nearly succeeded in conquering the Earth. During this time, the Avengers extended membership to Jack in gratitude for his efforts, and he readily accepted. The Avengers also developed a new strain of neutro-mist that allowed Jack to exist safely outside his armor for short periods of time.\nJack appeared to give his life while assisting the Avengers, leaving into space so as to not harm Earth with his explosion of Zero energy. However, his body was apparently reanimated by the Scarlet Witch. ''Jack'' returned to the mansion and abruptly exploded, killing Scott Lang and damaging the Mansion grounds.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/86.jpg');
