INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (782,'1516605131-1545','Snake-Eyes','https://www.superherodb.com/snake-eyes/10-10437/',0,0,0,0,0,0,'-','No alter egos found.','Xanthian Boulder Crusher','-','Marvel Team-Up Annual Vol 1 #7 October, 1984','Marvel Comics','bad','Male','Animal','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','-','-','','-','Snake-Eyes''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/snake-eyes/10-10437/history/','After the Collector left earth, Marrina decided to track down Snake-Eyes. She tracked him to an aquarium in New York City, only to discover he had been taken back to the ocean by the young adventures, Power Pack. Together, they were able to capture Snake-Eyes in a sunken ship and then move that ship to the Arctic where Snake-Eyes entered hibernation.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10437.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (784,'1516607721-4768','Hawkeye II','https://www.superherodb.com/hawkeye-ii/10-10043/',50,10,10,10,25,50,'Katherine Elizabeth Bishop','No alter egos found.','Kate Bishop','New York City, New York','Young Avengers #1 (April, 2005)','Marvel Comics','good','Female','Human','5''5 // 165 cm','126 lb // 57 kg','Blue','Black','Student; Adventurer; Fugitive','Bishop Publishing, New York City, New York','Young Avengers,Avengers','Derek Bishop (father); Eleanor Bishop (mother, deceased); Susan Bishop (sister);','Hawkeye II''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/hawkeye-ii/10-10043/history/','Along with the rest of his team, Hawkeye sided with Captain America and the Secret Avengers against the Superhuman Registration Act, which led to the Superhero Civil War.\nKate also unwittingly berates a resurrected Clint for donning the Captain America uniform and bearing the Captain America''s Shield. She stated that she took on the codename \"Hawkeye\" to honor the original Hawkeye, and not to mimic him or disgrace his memory. It was her words that convinced Clint to condemn Stark for his behavior, and go his own path.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10043.jpg');
