INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (1098,'1516609178-6827','Bushido','https://www.superherodb.com/bushido/10-1541/',40,10,10,10,20,70,'Ryuko Orsono','No alter egos found.','-','-','Titans: Secret Files & Origins #2','DC Comics','good','Male','Human','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','-','-','','-','Bushido''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/bushido/10-1541/history/','Bushido became a Black Lantern during Blackest Night. He was one of the Black Lanterns brought to Earth-Prime by Alex Luthor to kill Superboy-Prime. However, Superboy-Prime willingly put on a Black Lantern ring, which metamorphed to Red from the amount of emotion he displayed. The resulting energy blast destroyed Black Lantern Bushido.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/1541.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (1101,'1516609787-7485','Batwoman V','https://www.superherodb.com/batwoman-v/10-10234/',85,10,30,25,30,80,'Katherine Rebecca Kane','No alter egos found.','-','-','52 #7 (June, 2006)','DC Comics','good','Female','Human','5''10 // 178 cm','- lb // 0 kg','Green','Red','-','Gotham City','Batman Family','Jacob Kane (father), Gabi Kane (mother; deceased), Beth Kane (twin sister), Mary Elizabeth \"Bette\" Kane (cousin), Catherine Hamilton-Kane (stepmother), Philip Kane (uncle), Kane Family','Batwoman V''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/batwoman-v/10-10234/history/','Eventually, the Kanes moved to Brussels in Belgium, where they worked with NATO. However, one day, when Gabi decided to take the girls out for the day, they were attacked and kidnapped by terrorists. Though military intelligence managed to locate the hostages, Jacob only managed to rescue Kate, as both Gabi and Beth had been killed. He had tried to prevent her from seeing the worst of it, but Kate was traumatized by the sight of her mother and sister''s corpses.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10234.jpg');
INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (1106,'1516604310-346','Walrus','https://www.superherodb.com/walrus/10-10058/',50,30,10,50,15,20,'Hubert Carpent','No alter egos found.','-','Brooklyn, New York','Defenders #131 (May, 1984)','Marvel Comics','bad','Male','Human','6''0 // 183 cm','360 lb // 162 kg','Blue','Black','Cab driver','-','','Humbert Carpenter (uncle)','Walrus''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/walrus/10-10058/history/','Hubert Carpenter was a New York City cab driver who lived with Humber, an eccentric uncle (who was also a mad scientist). Humber used experimental technology to enhance Hubert''s physical abilities. Apparently, the dim-witted individual decided to do nothing more with his powers than to make a life of petty crime.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10058.jpg');
