INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (1214,'1516605308-1707','Shang-Chi','https://www.superherodb.com/shang-chi/10-454/',65,15,30,50,30,100,'Shang-Chi','No alter egos found.','The Master of Kung Fu; The Rising and Advancing of the Spirit; Chinaman (by Jack Tarr)','-','Special Marvel Edition #15 (December, 1973)','Marvel Comics','good','Male','Human','5''10 // 178 cm','175 lb // 79 kg','Brown','Black','-','-','','Fu Manchu, father; unnamed mother; Fah Lo Suee, (half-sister); Whispering Shadow (half-brother, deceased)','Shang-Chi''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/shang-chi/10-454/history/','Months later, the threat of his father rose again. Shang-Chi''s former allies of MI-6 sought his help once more, and Shang-Chi helped the team infiltrate his father''s base. There, Shang-Chi was confronted by a brother, of sorts: Moving Shadow, a man raised in the same manner as Shang-Chi but following his father''s commands to kill. Shang-Chi hoped to convince Moving Shadow to deny their father''s wishes, but they fought to a standstill and his father ultimately killed Moving Shadow for his supposed failure. At the same time, the agents of MI-6 succeeded in sabotaging his fatherÃ¯Â¿Â½s doomsday weapon. Shang-Chi stayed in the collapsing headquarters to verify that his father''s body was buried in the rubble, barely escaping himself. With his father once again thwarted, Shang-Chi returned to his fishing village.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/454.jpg');
