INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (1970,'1516608976-6576','Cerebra','https://www.superherodb.com/cerebra/10-1512/',0,0,0,0,0,0,'Shakti Haddad','No alter egos found.','-','-','X-Men 2099 #1 (October, 1993)','Marvel Comics','good','Female','Mutant','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','-','-','','Zail Haddad (father)','Cerebra''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/cerebra/10-1512/history/','Shakti Haddad, nicknamed Cerebra, was an employee of the Stark/Fujikawa Corporation in 2099, when XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an Chi Xan enticed her away to use her mutant powers to gather mutants together to join his new X-Men. After inviting Timothy Fitzgerald to XiÃ¯Â¿Â½anÃ¯Â¿Â½s gathering, Cerebra took up her position monitoring the Neuvo Sol Arcology. But the Synge Corporation attempted an assassin of XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an, and then attacked the gathering, believing XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an to be responsible for their founder, Noah SyngeÃ¯Â¿Â½s, murder. With XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an injured, Cerebra took charge and led the X-Men out of the arcology. While Krystalin, Metalhead, and Meanstreak broke into the Synge Corporation to prove XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an innocence, Cerebra stayed behind with XiÃ¯Â¿Â½anÃ¯Â¿Â½s naturally healing body. But Junkpile soon attacked, and Cerebra and the X-Men were helpless to stop him from taking XiÃ¯Â¿Â½anÃ¯Â¿Â½s body. Then, Cerebra led a group of the remaining X-Men to the Synge Corporation to free their captured fellows. Serpentina was later killed in another fight with Junkpile, who was finally disabled by an evolved and revived XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/1512.jpg');
