INSERT INTO superhero VALUES (3214,'1516607184-3984','Junkpile','https://www.superherodb.com/junkpile/10-10002/',50,40,20,90,85,30,'-','No alter egos found.','-','-','X-Men 2099 #1 (October, 1993)','Marvel Comics','bad','Male','Mutant','- // 0 cm','- lb // 0 kg','-','-','Mercenary; Former member of S.H.I.E.L.D.','-','','-','Junkpile''s history','https://www.superherodb.com/junkpile/10-10002/history/','Junkpile was a member of the X-Men and an ex-member of XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an Chi XanÃ¯Â¿Â½s Lawless in 2099, when his disagreements with XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an made him turn on his fellow teammates. Since XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an had come back from Saigon with visions of peace between human and mutantkind, Junkpile felt that he had strayed from his destiny. Junkpile believed that mutants were born with the power to do what they wanted, and to try to work for peace with weaker humans would degrade them. So that when the Synge Corporation thought XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an had murdered their founder, Noah Synge, Junkpile gave them enough information to raid XiÃ¯Â¿Â½anÃ¯Â¿Â½s gathering and kill him. But the assassination failed, and Junkpile was forced to fight his ex-teammates and kidnap an injured XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an. As Junkpile had installed a psionic jammer that kept Cerebra out of his head, Serpentina wasnÃ¯Â¿Â½t strong enough to hurt him, and Timothy Fitzgerald couldnÃ¯Â¿Â½t use his powers properly, taking XiÃ¯Â¿Â½anÃ¯Â¿Â½s body was easy. After returning to the Synge Corporations headquarters with XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an, Junkpile later stopped Krystalin from killing the corporationÃ¯Â¿Â½s new head, Lytton Synge, and then fought the X-Men that had come to save XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an and clear his name. Serpentina attacked him impulsively, and he killed her by shoving her face against the wall, which galvanized the rest of the X-Men to attack him. But none of them were strong enough to hurt him until XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an appeared revived and used the disintegrating power of his left hand to disable Junkpile. And though Junkpile threatened that if XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an didnÃ¯Â¿Â½t kill him, he would come after him, XiÃ¯Â¿Â½an believed he would eventually see his mistake and return as a friend, and so let him live.','','','','','','','','/pictures2/portraits/10/100/10002.jpg');
